The average monthly price for on-peak hours in the Northwest from August=20
through March is $60 a megawatt-hour - a fraction of what it was three month=
s=20
ago. Many in the western electricity industry think that's because FERC's=20
price controls have kept prices artificially low. A smaller group thinks the=
