opportunities to develop some new energy technologies," said Nick Hughes,=20
environmental policy adviser to the British oil multinational BP Plc.=20
"Now that those elements are there and there's an opportunity to do somethin=
g=20
on a global scale, the ball is really rolling."=20
Green investment funds springing up everywhere are not just focussing on the=
=20
obvious alternative energy plays.=20
Emma Howard Boyd runs the Environmental Research Unit of British fund Jupite=
r=20
Asset Management, managing two green funds worth about 230 million pounds=20
($330 million).=20
About 70 percent of her funds are in "solution providers" like Danish wind=20
power stock Vestas and the British public transport operation FirstGroup tha=
t=20
is involved in testing fuel cell powered buses.=20
