"It's not a revolution we are looking at here, it's mainly about doing=20
existing things better," said David Kernohan, Manager of the Energy=20
Environment Service at the consultancy Cambridge Econometrics.=20
"The new fuel technologies and fuel efficiency improvements achieved by the=20
energy producers and motor manufacturers are major achievements, even if not=
=20
very flamboyant ones."=20
